# Patch: kimchi-dev runtime extensions for pi-coding-agent
#
# NOTE for upgraders: `pnpm patch-commit` regenerates this file and strips this
# header. Re-add metadata only, then run `pnpm install` to refresh the lockfile
# hash. Functional changes must be made through the pnpm patch workspace.
#
# Changes included:
#   1. Expose KIMCHI_API_KEY in --help.
#   2. Support forced compaction for small sessions.
#   3. Add previewTheme and showError to ExtensionUIContext.
#   4. Preserve Kimchi-specific provider/model selection and TUI presentation,
#      with multi-model state keyed per session: ModelSelectorComponent takes a
#      sessionId constructor parameter, and all reads/writes of
#      process.__kimchiMultiModelEnabled and process.__kimchiOrchestratorRef go
#      through Map<sessionId, value> instead of plain globals (see
#      src/extensions/kimchi-process.ts for the owning declarations).
#   5. Preserve the UserMessageComponent.contentBox compatibility field.
#   6. Await asynchronous JSONL export.
#   7. Destroy child stdio streams after a timeout kill so escaped grandchildren
#      cannot keep the bash tool call open indefinitely.
#
# Removed during the 0.80.5 rebase because upstream now provides them:
#   - Next-turn refresh of active tools/model/thinking state:
#     https://github.com/earendil-works/pi/pull/6176
#   - before_provider_headers hook registration, types, runner, and SDK wiring:
#     https://github.com/earendil-works/pi/pull/6350
#
# Tracking: inherited from the pre-0.80.5 patch. The repository records an
# upstream PR plan but no filed issue/PR URL for the remaining changes yet. The
# bash timeout fix is tracked by the local change originally merged as #833.
# Removal criteria: upstream exposes forced compaction, previewTheme/showError,
# and the remaining UI fixes; Kimchi-specific provider/model behavior moves to
# public extension APIs; and upstream's bash runner destroys child stdio after
# timeout termination or otherwise guarantees waitForChildProcess cannot hang
# on escaped descendants.
#
